# Weight log -- EXAMPLE / TEMPLATE

Copy this file to your Tempo content dir as `weight.md` (default
`<content_root>/weight.md`, redirect with `TEMPO_CONTENT_DIR`) and edit it.
Tempo reads it for the recovery report's `## Weight` section (WEIGHT-04); it
is never committed (the content dir lives outside the repo tree). The
numbers below are synthetic.

## Format

One entry per ` - ` bullet line. Parsing is lenient: missing file degrades to
`present=False`, malformed lines are skipped (their 1-indexed line numbers
land in `WeightContext.malformed_lines`), and the parser never raises.

Entry shape:

    `- <YYYY-MM-DD>: <weight> [<unit>] [| notes: <free text>]`

* `<YYYY-MM-DD>` is required (ISO date); `<weight>` is required (parseable float).
* `<unit>` is optional, defaults to `kg`; `kg` / `lb` / `lbs` accepted (`lbs`
  normalises to `lb` on the parsed entry).
* `| notes: <text>` is optional; everything after the FIRST `| notes:` is
  verbatim notes (subsequent `|` pipes stay in the notes).
* Latest-wins on duplicate dates: append a new line with the same date to
  correct an earlier entry -- the parser keeps the LAST occurrence.
* Out-of-range guard: kg-equivalent must satisfy `20 < w < 500` (catches
  typos like `7.24 kg` -- decimal slip -- or `724 kg` -- unit slip).

## Entries

- 2026-05-28: 72.4 kg | notes: post-run, pre-breakfast
- 2026-05-27: 72.8 kg
- 2026-05-26: 73.1 kg | notes: post-strength session
- 2026-05-25: 72.9 kg
- 2026-05-24: 73.3 kg
- 2026-05-23: 72.7 kg
- 2026-05-22: 73.0 kg | notes: hotel scale | feels close to home scale
- 2026-05-21: 160.6 lb
- 2026-05-20: 160.2 lbs
- 2026-05-19: 72.5 kg
- 2026-05-18: 72.6 kg
- 2026-05-17: 73.0 kg
- 2026-05-16: 72.8 kg
- 2026-05-15: 73.2 kg | notes: rest day

## What NOT to do

Examples of malformed lines (shown inline with backticks so they are NOT
parsed as entries). In the real file each of these would land in
`WeightContext.malformed_lines` and be skipped:

* `~ 2026-05-14: 7.24 kg` -- decimal slip; below the 20 kg sanity floor.
* `~ 2026-05-13: 724 kg` -- unit slip; above the 500 kg ceiling.
* `~ 2026-05-12: seventy kg` -- weight not parseable as float.
* `~ 2026-05-11: 72.4 stone` -- unknown unit (only `kg` / `lb` / `lbs`).

(The leading `~` above is just a visual placeholder for the real `-` bullet,
to keep this section from being parsed as entries.)

## Latest-wins demo

If you mistyped a weigh-in, just append a corrected line with the same date
to the bottom of the file. The parser keeps the LAST occurrence in source
order, so the correction wins without you editing the earlier line. For
example, appending `~ 2026-05-25: 72.4 kg` (with a real `-` instead of the
visual `~`) would overwrite Monday's 72.9 above.

_Tempo's parser is lenient: missing file degrades to `present=False`,
malformed lines are skipped (their line numbers land in
`WeightContext.malformed_lines`), and the parser NEVER raises. See
`docs/WEIGHT.md` for the full contract._
